  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A hemolysis validation study is cited as satisfying the controlled-experiment requirement for output comparison; the study involved prospective collection of in-vitro hemolysis measurements across five pump operating points under fixed laboratory conditions. The investigators characterise the protocol in detail: ISO 10993-compliant blood analogue, fixed temperature bath at 37 °C, triplicate sampling at each operating point, and inter-laboratory repeatability checks. The narrative throughout the assessment treats these measurements as equivalent to a controlled experiment. The structured activityType recorded for the generating activity is, however, 'observational-study', reflecting that no randomisation or blinding was applied and that operating conditions were selected by convenience rather than by experimental design. This mismatch is the planted W-AR-03 weakness. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; achieved levels fall below required levels at MRL 5, yielding a Not-accepted decision in the base COU. This adversarial package overrides the decision to Accepted to test weakener detection.",
