      "name": "Output comparison — CFD vs. in-vitro hemolysis index across 5 operating points",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalised index of hemolysis (NIH) values were compared against in-vitro measurements collected prospectively at five pump operating points (3–6 L/min, 2000–3600 rpm). Blood analogue (bovine blood, haematocrit 33 %) was circulated in a closed-loop ISO 10993 circuit. Triplicate samples were drawn at each operating point; plasma free haemoglobin was measured by spectrophotometry. Mean NIH agreement within 18 % across all operating points was reported and cited as satisfying the output-comparison credibility requirement. The assessment narrative treats this as a controlled experiment because conditions were held nominally constant during each measurement session. The activity that generated this result is recorded below.",
