      "rationale": "CFD predictions were compared against in-vitro NIH measurements across all five operating points. Mean agreement was within 18 %, marginally exceeding the 15 % acceptance criterion. The supporting validation activity is described in the literature as a rigorous in-vitro protocol with ISO 10993-compliant equipment and triplicate sampling, which the assessment team judged sufficient to satisfy the controlled-experiment requirement. Achieved level 3 against required level 4. Note: the structured record of the generating activity carries activityType 'observational-study', which does not satisfy the requiredVerificationMethod 'controlled-experiment' specified in the binding requirement."
