    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The assessment team concluded that the in-vitro hemolysis validation study, conducted under ISO 10993-compliant conditions with triplicate sampling and inter-session repeatability checks, constitutes adequate experimental evidence to satisfy the output-comparison requirement. The Monte Carlo UQ bounds prediction uncertainty within acceptable limits for regulatory submission. Although achieved credibility levels fall below required levels across multiple factors, the team judged that the combination of the detailed in-vitro protocol and the UQ analysis provides sufficient confidence in the hemolysis predictions for the VAD COU. The output-comparison validation result is cited as meeting the controlled-experiment requirement on the basis of the rigorous laboratory protocol described in the supporting documentation.",
